.TH diodmount 8 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
diodmount \- mount diod file systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B diodmount
.I "[OPTIONS]"
.I HOST:/dir
.I dir
.LP
.B diodmount
.I "--list-exports HOST"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diodmount
is the mount utility for the distributed I/O daemon.
.LP
This command must be run as root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I "-x, --list-exports HOST"
List file systems exported by HOST.
.TP
.I "-u, --mount-user USER"
If USER is not root, causes the file system to be mounted so that only
USER can access it.  Default is to mount as root.
.TP
.I "-n, --no-mtab"
Do not update /etc/mtab.  This may be appropriate, for example, when
the file system is mounted in a private name space.
.I "-o, --diod-options OPT,[OPT,...]"
Pass additional 9P mount options when mounting the \fBdiod\fR server.
Options specified in this way override the options that \fBdiodmount\fR
sets up internally.
.TP
.I "-O, --diodctl-options OPT,[OPT,...]"
Pass additional 9P mount when mouting the \fBdiodctl\fR server.
Options specified in this way override the options that \fBdiodmount\fR
sets up internally.
.TP
.I "-d, --direct"
Mount the \fBdiod\fR server directly without first mounting \fBdiodctl\fR
to determine the port.  This must be used in conjunction with
\fI-o port=PORT\fR.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.LP
List the file systems exported by tycho42:
.nf
    diodmount -x tycho42
.fi
.LP
Mount /g/g99 from tycho42, so that all users can access it:
.nf
    diodmount tycho42:/g/g99 /g/g99
.fi
.LP
Mount tycho42's diodctl server directly for testing:
.nf
    diodmount tycho42:/diodctl /g/g99
.fi
.LP
Mount /p/lcrater1 on tycho[101-164], with a private server for garlick:
.nf
    pdsh -w tycho[101-164] \\
        diodmount -u garlick tycho42:/p/lcrater1 /p/lcrater1
.fi
.nf
.SH "SEE ALSO"
diod (8),
diodctl (8),
diod.conf (5)
